	(403,73,'venue_0_venue_description','Most of Theatre@First\'s shows take place at a venue in or near <a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/8fWhM\">Davis Square, Somerville</a>. If you are driving, Davis Square is at the intersection of Elm St, Highland Ave, College Ave, and Holland Ave; it is just south of Powderhouse Circle (Broadway and Powder House Blvd), east of Teele Square (Curtis St and Broadway), and west of Porter Square, Cambridge (Massachusetts Ave). Parking is available at metered spots on the street and in several public parking lots within a 5-minute walk.\r\n\r\nVia the MBTA, Davis Square can be reached directly by the Red Line subway (Davis Square station) or by several bus routes, including #\'s 80, 87, 88, 90, 94, &amp; 96. You can also take the 77 bus to the corner of Massachusetts Ave and Dover St and walk about 5 minutes north on Dover St to Davis Square.'),
	(404,73,'_venue_0_venue_description','field_5599952e4090c'),
	(405,73,'venue_1_venue_name','Unity Somerville'),
	(406,73,'_venue_1_venue_name','field_559994ba40909'),
	(407,73,'venue_1_venue_address','6 William Street\r\nSomerville, MA 02144'),
	(408,73,'_venue_1_venue_address','field_559994cd4090a'),
	(409,73,'venue_1_venue_description','<a href=\"http://www.unitygreaterboston.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Unity Somerville</a> is located four blocks up College Avenue from Davis Square, on the left side of the street, at the corner of William Street and College Avenue. The entrance to the theater is at the front of the building, on William Street.'),
	(410,73,'_venue_1_venue_description','field_5599952e4090c'),
	(411,73,'venue_2_venue_name','The Somerville Theatre'),
	(412,73,'_venue_2_venue_name','field_559994ba40909'),
	(413,73,'venue_2_venue_address','55 Davis Square\r\nSomerville, MA 02144'),
	(414,73,'_venue_2_venue_address','field_559994cd4090a'),
	(415,73,'venue_2_venue_description','<a href=\"http://feitheatres.com/somerville-theatre/directions/\" target=\"_blank\">The Somerville Theatre</a> is located in the heart of Davis Square, next to the Holland Street exit of the Davis Square MBTA Red Line station.'),
	(416,73,'_venue_2_venue_description','field_5599952e4090c'),
	(417,73,'venue_3_venue_name','The Davis Square Theatre'),
	(418,73,'_venue_3_venue_name','field_559994ba40909'),
	(419,73,'venue_3_venue_address','255 Elm Street\r\nSomerville, MA 02144'),
	(420,73,'_venue_3_venue_address','field_559994cd4090a'),
	(421,73,'venue_3_venue_description','<a href=\"http://www.davissquaretheatre.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The Davis Square Theatre</a> is also in the heart of Davis Square, on Elm Street. Look for the Davis Square Theatre marquis next to Found (a consignment store); the theater is located down the stairs and to the right, across from Saloon.'),
	(422,73,'_venue_3_venue_description','field_5599952e4090c'),
	(423,73,'venue_4_venue_name','Elizabeth Peabody House (EPH)'),
	(424,73,'_venue_4_venue_name','field_559994ba40909'),
	(425,73,'venue_4_venue_address','277 Broadway\r\nSomerville, MA 02145'),
	(426,73,'_venue_4_venue_address','field_559994cd4090a'),
	(427,73,'venue_4_venue_description','<a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=277+Broadway,+Somerville,+MA+02145&amp;sll=42.396175,-71.105103&amp;sspn=0.021393,0.039911&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=16&amp;iwloc=addr\" target=\"new\">Find us using Google maps</a>\r\n\r\nTo get to the <a href=\"http://teph.org/\">Elizabeth Peabody House</a> by public transport:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EPH is about a mile NW (on Broadway) from Sullivan Station on the MBTA Orange Line</li>\r\n	<li>EPH is about two miles SE (on Broadway) from Porter/Davis Squares on the MBTA Red LIne</li>\r\n	<li>The #89 bus passes EPH between Sullivan Station and the Clarendon Hill Busway. It also passes Powderhouse Square, just up College Ave from Davis Square.</li>\r\n	<li>The #101 bus passes EPH between Sullivan Station and Malden Center Station.</li>\r\n	<li>See <a href=\"http://www.mbta.com/\">www.mbta.com</a> for more detailed schedules and routes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo get there from Route 93:\r\nGoing North from Boston, use Exit 29.\r\nGoing South from the North Shore, use Exit 30 (Mystic Ave)\r\nEither way, you then:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Follow signs for Route 28 South</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right at Broadway and McGrath Highway (Near a park, Dunkin Donuts, and two gas stations.)</li>\r\n	<li>EPH is about three blocks up Broadway, on your right.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere are several municipal parking areas nearby on Broadway. On-street parking without need for a resident permit is available on Broadway, Grant, Wheatland and Fellsway West (unmetered after 6:00p.m.). The Foss Park parking lot is closed at night, but is available for use during the Sunday matinee.'),
	(428,73,'_venue_4_venue_description','field_5599952e4090c'),
	(429,73,'venue','5'),
	(430,73,'_venue','field_5599947240908'),
